[
  "Together with his brother Wolfgang, Michael Herz derives his fortune from two of Germany's most recognized companies: Tchibo and Beiersdorf.",
  "Their father, Max, along with Carl Tchiling-Hiryan, founded Tchibo, which imports and sells coffee, in 1949. Max passed away in 1965.",
  "Tchibo expanded into retailing a range of other consumer goods and services including electronics, travel and mobile telephony.",
  "Family holding company maxingvest ag owns 100% of Tchibo and about 47% of listed skin-care company Beiersdorf, whose brands include Nivea.",
  "Older brother Guenter and sister Daniela Herz-Schnoeckel were bought out in 2003."
]